From 1a2a5ddda9f73a1ce9f8145e8795126ba9159e57 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 22:36:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] init: skip privileged cmds, cgroup writes, and SELinux in
 container mode

Additional LXC container adaptations building on the existing InContainerMode()
detection:

libbegetutil.versionscript: export InContainerMode, InUpdaterMode, InRescueMode,
and InRepairMode symbols so they are accessible from shared libraries that link
libbegetutil (e.g. selinuxadp).

init.cfg, init.without_two_stages.cfg: change the post-fs rootfs remount from
ro to rw. Inside the LXC container the rootfs is already mounted read-write by
the host; attempting to remount ro fails and blocks the boot sequence.

init_common_cmds.c: skip DoChown, DoChmod, and DoMount when in container mode.
These operations either fail on the read-write container rootfs or attempt
mounts that the container namespace does not permit.

init_cgroup.c: skip ProcessServiceDied and ProcessServiceAdd when in container
mode. Cgroup v1 paths (/dev/blkio, /dev/cpuset, etc.) are not accessible inside
the LXC namespace.

init_service.c: disable sandbox (g_enableSandbox=false) and skip
SetServiceEnterSandbox in container mode to prevent mount-namespace pivot_root
failures inside LXC.

selinux/BUILD.gn: add libbegetutil dep so selinuxadp can call InContainerMode.
selinux/selinux_adp.c: skip LoadSelinuxPolicy, SetServiceContent, and
SetServiceSaspawnContent in container mode. The Ubuntu Touch host owns the
SELinux policy; loading the OHOS policy inside the container fails and blocks
all service label transitions.

Part of Phase 1 (infrastructure & target setup) and Phase 3 (core service
stability) for hybris_generic.

Change-Id: I6ad2f6744dfca8c72afa81d3c0a538d1ce7c872b
